Our design system lives inside `/src/app/` and follows a layered structure:

- **Foundations** → `/foundations/`
  - `primitive/` defines core variables (colors, dimensions, typography).
  - `base/` defines reusable token sets (actions, icons, effects).
  - `semantic/` defines responsive tokens for spacing, grid, typography, and color (light/dark themes).
- **Utils** → `/utils/` includes motion and font utilities.
- **Integration** → `/integration/` maps design tokens to Builder.io props.

Use tokens defined in `/styles/tokens.css` (which imports all layers).
Reference CSS variables directly, e.g.:
- Spacing: `var(--sp-md)`
- Typography: `var(--ty-body-md-fs)` or `var(--ty-title-lg-lh)`
- Colors: `var(--color-bg-sf-base)`, `var(--color-ct-pri)`
- Borders & Elevation: `var(--color-bd-faint)`, `var(--color-el-2)`

When generating new sections, always use:
- Tokens instead of px values.
- `var(--token-name)` syntax for colors, spacing, and typography.
- Grid and spacing conventions from the semantic layer (e.g. `sp-none`, `sp-sm`, `sp-md`, etc.)

Fonts should use:
`font-family: var(--ff-sans);`
